# Tell Azure Oryx to skip Node.js build steps.
# The React frontend is pre-built by CI (npm run build in frontend/) and the
# resulting dist/ folder is included in the deployment artifact.  Oryx must
# NOT re-run npm install / npm run build because:
#   1. The root package.json targets the Replit workspace, not the deployable app.
#   2. Oryx may pick the wrong Node version or run build from the wrong directory.
#   3. A failed Oryx Node build would overwrite the pre-built frontend/dist/.
#
# Python dependencies are still installed by Oryx (requirements.txt).
nodejs
